<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="226" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,367,392]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Remarks</emphasis>
. The most distinctive feature of this species is the digitate process on the apophysis of the style. The basal tooth-like process of the aedeagal shaft in lateral view suggests an association with the shaft, but in posterior or ventroposterior view the process appears associated with the atrium or preatrium. The styles of other species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stiller, 2019" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[151,289,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[151,289,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Discolopeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a single, small and short subapical or apical ventral tooth. The apophysis of the style of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thigmacaenus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">D. thigmacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[369,538,513,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetracaenus">
<emphasis box="[369,538,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">D. tetracaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is weakly sclerotized, curvate, setose medially, but in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[1183,1352,513,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetracaenus">
<emphasis box="[1183,1352,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">D. tetracaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a digitate process. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[347,541,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thigmacaenus">
<emphasis box="[347,541,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">D. thigmacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[559,646,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,194,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 12a–i. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., habitus, dorsally. a. Wiedouw, male; b. Gifberg, female; c. Wiedouw, female; d. Gifberg, male; e. Nymph, Gifberg; f, hind wing, male; g, tegmina, male; h, hind wing female; i, tegmina, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626835/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs 12</figureCitation>
a–d) resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[830,1011,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viraktamathi">
<emphasis box="[830,1011,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">D. viraktamathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in coloration (
<figureCitation box="[1186,1273,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[186,1401,196,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[186,1401,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 17a–h. Discolopeus viraktamathi n.gen. &amp; sp., habitus. a, b, c. Cradock, male, dorsally, female, dorsally and laterally, respectively; d, e, f. Waterpoort, male, female, nymph, respectively, dorsally; g, tegmina, male; h, hind wing male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626845/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs 17</figureCitation>
a–e), and to a lesser extent 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[302,408,585,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctus">
<emphasis box="[302,408,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">D. arctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has fewer markings on the crown (
<figureCitation box="[904,1037,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,193,1393]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,193,1395]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8a–j. Discolopeus arctus n. gen. &amp; sp., habitus. a, b. Male and female respectively, dorsally; c, d. Male and female respectively, laterally; e, f. Nymphs, early and late instar, dorsally; g, h. Face, male and female, respectively; i, hind wing; j, tegmina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626827/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs 8a, 8b</figureCitation>
). The point distribution map of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetracaenus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">D. tetracaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in 
<figureCitation box="[343,438,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1496,1518]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1466]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,193,1474]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 19a–c. Distribution maps of leafhopper species of Discolopeus gen.n. and associated plants. a. Hyaenanche globosa near Vanrhynsdorp and one record near Citrusdal (red squares); b. Potential natural distribution of D. copeus sp.n. in the southwestern parts of South Africa, Western Cape Province; c. Point distributions of D. colopeus sp.n., D. lissus sp.n., D. tetracaenus sp.n., D. thigmacaenus sp.n., D. triacaenus sp.n. and D. viraktamathi sp.n. in Western, Northern and Eastern Cape Provinces." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626849/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 19c</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
